<LI><A HREF="ftp:/ftp.eff.org/pub/CAF/statements/caf-statement"> 
ftp:/ftp.eff.org/pub/CAF/statements/caf-statement</A><BR>
This site clarifies some of the terms that go along with privacy on the internet. It gives the definitions of words that are located in the rules regarding the internet. It
would be very helpful in clarifying some of the rules and regulations regarding the world wide web.
<LI><A HREF="http://www.eff.org/CAF/cafuiuc.html">http://www.eff.org/CAF/cafuiuc.html</A><BR>
This site gives some answers to possible questions about the censorship of sex and sex-related issues on the internet. It also gives links to stories about cases involving
the censorship of sex and sex-related issues. Additionally, the site gives links to other sites where more information on the topic may be found. 
<LI><A HREF="ftp://ftp.eff.org/pub/CAF/academic/student.freedoms.aaup">ftp://ftp.eff.org/pub/CAF/academic/student.freedoms.aaup</A><BR>
This site has the policy statement written by the American Association of University Professors called the Joint Statement on Rights and Freedoms of Students. It basically
   says what students can and cannot do, which includes the internet.
<LI><A HREF="http://zippy.sonoma.edu:70/0h/ProjectCensored/AboutPC.html">http://zippy.sonoma.edu:70/0h/ProjectCensored/AboutPC.html</A><BR>
This site is about Project Censored(PC).  PC explores and publicizes the extent of censorship in our society.
Their research should help me in my search for cases of censorship on the internet.
<LI><A HREF="http://www.efnh.org/efnh/">http://www.efnh.org/efnh/</A><BR>
This site is the home page of the New Hampshire Electronic Frontiers Foundation(EFF). The EFF is a public 
interest advocacy group that is concerned about the protection of civil liberties in the on-line world. 
</OL>
